The [sans-serif](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sans-serif) [DejaVu font](http://dejavu.sourceforge.net/) is included on every Webconverger distribution since version 2.21.

# Installing the default Webconverger fonts on a Debian/Ubuntu machine:

  1. `monty:~% sudo apt-get install ttf-dejavu`
  2. Restart your browser

# On other operating systems:

 * [DejaVu download](http://dejavu.sourceforge.net/wiki/index.php/Download)

# Microsoft fonts

The package [msttcorefonts](http://packages.qa.debian.org/m/msttcorefonts.html)
contains the familiar Microsoft fonts like Arial, Verdana etc. 

Since there are license and freedom issues shipping these proprietary fonts
with Webconverger, they have been dropped.
